cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about adversarial attacks on computer vision tasks, specifically object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes a generative mechanism and a GAN framework, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the transferability of the generated adversarial examples, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with video data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing attacking methods, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
